Applicable Licenses
_____________________

DMFC is built upon a number of other open source technologies and products.  Third party Java software binary archives that are bundled with the the DMFC application are listed below:

	jing.jar
	Relax NG Schema Validator
	Jing Copying Conditions
	http://www.thaiopensource.com/relaxng/copying.html

	saxon.jar
	XSLT Processor
	1.0 Mozilla Public License
	http://www.mozilla.org/MPL/MPL-1.0.html
	
	saxon8.jar
	XML/XSLT Mapping to Java
	1.0 Mozilla Public License
	http://www.mozilla.org/MPL/MPL-1.0.html
	
	saxon8-dom.jar
	Saxon-DOM support
	1.0 Mozilla Public License
	http://www.mozilla.org/MPL/MPL-1.0.html

	batik-css
	CSS parser conforming to the SAC API.
	Apache License, Version 2
	http://www.apache.org/licenses/
	
	batik-util
	Apache License, Version 2
	http://www.apache.org/licenses/

	sac.jar
	Simple API for CSS
	http://www.w3.org/Style/CSS/SAC/doc/org/w3c/css/sac/package-tree.html
	W3C Software License
	http://www.w3.org/Consortium/Legal/2002/copyright-software-20021231

	chardet.jar
	Java port of Mozilla's Automatic Charset Detection
	1.0 Mozilla Public License
	http://www.mozilla.org/MPL/MPL-1.0.html

	tagsoup.jar
	SAX-compliant parser of Java/HTML found in the wild
	http://home.ccil.org/~cowan/XML/tagsoup/
	Licensed under both the GNU GPL version 2.0 and 
	The Academic Free License
	http://www.opensource.org/licenses/afl-3.0.php
	
	xercesImpl.jar
	Java Parser for SAX and DOM
	http://xerces.apache.org/xerces-j/api.html
	The Apache Software License, Version 1.1
	http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE

	icu.jar
	Unicode and Internationalization support
	X License/ICU License
	http://www-306.ibm.com/software/globalization/icu/license.jsp

	wstx-lgpl-2.0.3.jar
	Woodstox XML processor
	http://woodstox.codehaus.org/
	High-performance validating namespace-aware StAX-compliant (JSR-173) Open Source XML-processor
	GNU General Public License
	http://www.gnu.org/licenses/licenses.html

	jl1.0.jar
	mp3 decoding (http://www.javazoom.net/javalayer/javalayer.html). 
	GNU Lesser General Public License
	http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html

The following software is required to run specific transformers, but the source code is not integrated in any way with the DMFC.  LAME and Python are included in the Windows installer and automatically installed.
	
	LAME
	mp3 encoding (http://www.mp3dev.org)
	GNU Lesser General Public License 
	http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html. 

	Python
	Object Oriented Programming Language
	The Python License
	http://www.python.org/psf/license.html


